FBIS4-15133 "drsov067_t_94002" FBIS-SOV-94-067 Daily Report 6 Apr 1994 BALTIC STATES Estonia Russia Sets New Conditions for Troop Withdrawal Russia Sets New Conditions for Troop Withdrawal LD0604121694 Tallinn Radio Tallinn Network in Estonian 1100 GMT 6 Apr 94 LD0604121694 Tallinn Radio Tallinn Network Estonian BFN [Text] Russia continues to set new additional conditions on Estonia for a troop withdrawal. This is stated in an Estonian Foreign Ministry statement disseminated in Moscow today. During the 18th round of Estonian-Russian interstate talks, which began yesterday in Moscow, the Russian side set a condition that Estonia should amend its legislation to enable all retired servicemen to qualify for residence permits, regardless of [words indistinct] they have lived in Estonia. [Words indistinct] to pay the $23 million as compensation toward the building of housing for the withdrawing servicemen on active service. The Estonian Foreign Ministry is puzzled by the Russian statement (?that it is unaware of international support given to Estonia). The Estonian side hopes that the negotiations today will be more constructive than they were yesterday and that Russia is prepared to hold talks over issues which are not in conflict with the existing Estonian legislation.
